  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Finding the inverse of a rational function</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<!--/*Find \(g^{-1}\)(x)\).*/-->
<p>Consider the function, \( \displaystyle g(x)=\frac{{@num@}}{{@denome@}} \)</p>
<p>Find the inverse function \( \displaystyle g^{-1}(x)\)</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\( \displaystyle g^{-1} (x) = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>
<p>[[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3></p>
<p>To find the inverse of the function, we follow the procedure below.<p> 
<p>1. Replace the \(g(x)\) in {@quest@} with \(y\).</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\( \displaystyle {@quest_1@} \)</p>

<p>2. Change all the \(x\)'s in the equation to \(y\), and all of the \(y\)'s to \(x\).</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\( \displaystyle{@quest_2@} \)</p>

<p>3. Make \(y\) subject of the formulae.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\( \displaystyle {@y3@} \)</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\( \displaystyle {@y4@} \)</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\( \displaystyle {@y5@} \)</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\( \displaystyle {@y6@} \)</p>

<p>4. Replace \(y\) with the inverse function.</p>
<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(g^{-1}(x)={@ta@}\)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
